A '''cullingey''' is an obsolete unit of mass that was used in the southern region in state of [[Karnataka]] in [[India]]. One cullingey was approximately equal to 81.25&nbsp;[[troy grain]]s (5.265&nbsp;g). After [[Metrication in India|metrification]] in the mid-20th century, the unit became obsolete.
