'''Estimated ultimate recovery''' or '''Expected ultimate recovery''' (EUR) of a resource is the sum of the [[proven reserves]] at a specific time and the [[Extraction of petroleum|cumulative production]] up to that time.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Morehouse|first=David F.|title=The Intricate Puzzle of Oil & Gas "Reserve Growth"|date=July 1997|journal=Natural Gas Monthly|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PnIj8pMHTdYC&pg=PR7 |accessdate=8 February 2012|publisher=[[Energy Information Administration]]}}</ref>

